<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-18593] CircleCI: Add separate approval step for oa utests on separate workflows</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-18593</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-14227&quot; title=&quot;Extend maximum expiration date&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-14227&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-14227&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; added new &lt;tt&gt;j*_utests_oa&lt;/tt&gt; jobs to run unit tests with the new, not-default &quot;oa&quot; sstable format. Those tests depend on the &lt;tt&gt;start_j*_unit_tests&lt;/tt&gt; approval step on the separate workflows.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, the separate workflow is meant to allow running jobs individually, and having a common approval step for both &lt;tt&gt;j*_unit_tests&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;j*_utests_oa&lt;/tt&gt; prevents us from doing so. That&apos;s the case for example of the development of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-18504&quot; title=&quot;Added support for type VECTOR&amp;lt;type, dimension&amp;gt;&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-18504&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-18504&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, where I want to run a single unit test job without caring about the specialization, but the common approval step forces me to run both jobs, duplicating the costs.&#160;An example run can be seen &lt;a href=&quot;https://app.circleci.com/pipelines/github/adelapena/cassandra/2948/workflows/67e5bfcd-c8df-4558-a889-c8828e8dd310&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think that &lt;tt&gt;j*_utests_oa&lt;/tt&gt; should have its own separate approval step, the same way that &lt;tt&gt;j*_utest_cdc&lt;/tt&gt;, &lt;tt&gt;j*_utest_fqltool&lt;/tt&gt;, &lt;tt&gt;j*_utest_compression&lt;/tt&gt; or &lt;tt&gt;j*_utest_system_keyspace_directory&lt;/tt&gt; have their own approval step.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
